@baseUrl = http://localhost:5116
@agentEmail = agent@supportops.local
@agentPassword = AgentPassword123!
@agentToken = replace-with-agent-access-token
@ticketId = replace-with-ticket-id

### Order
# 1. Create a ticket as a customer from tickets.http.
# 2. Wait for the worker to process the queued triage job.
# 3. Run Login agent and copy accessToken into @agentToken.
# 4. Run Get triage result.
# 5. Run one review action: Approve triage, Edit triage, Reject triage, or Retry triage.
#    Retry is most useful when no triage job is queued or processing and you want to request a new triage run.

### Login agent
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{agentEmail}}",
  "password": "{{agentPassword}}"
}

### Get triage result
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets/{{ticketId}}/triage
Authorization: Bearer {{agentToken}}

### Approve triage
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets/{{ticketId}}/triage/approve
Authorization: Bearer {{agentToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "notes": "Recommendation looks correct for the demo ticket."
}

### Edit triage
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets/{{ticketId}}/triage/edit
Authorization: Bearer {{agentToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "category": "Technical",
  "priority": "High",
  "notes": "Adjusted after agent review."
}

### Reject triage
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets/{{ticketId}}/triage/reject
Authorization: Bearer {{agentToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "reason": "Recommendation does not match the ticket details."
}

### Retry triage
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets/{{ticketId}}/triage/retry
Authorization: Bearer {{agentToken}}
